N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 11ยง 1.2 - Order

State Regulations

An order is an official act of the superintendent of particular application, including approval, licensing, revocation or suspension of a license, refusal of a license, issuance or refusal of a permit, order for examination of an insurer, and like official acts having legal consequences. Notes
